te is set to an unrelated case, it will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not be able to process the action, which is considered an application logic error and will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"emit runtime warnings."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This can happen if another reducer in the parent domain changes the child state to an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unrelated case when it handles the action "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"before"}]},{"type":"text","text":" the scoped reducer runs. For example, a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent may receive a dismissal action from the child domain:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Reduce { state, action in","  switch action {","  case .loggedIn(.quitButtonTapped):","    state = .loggedOut(LoggedOut.State())","  \/\/ ...","  }","}","Scope(state: \/State.loggedIn, action: \/Action.loggedIn) {","  LoggedIn()  \/\/ ⚠️ Logged-in domain can't handle `quitButtonTapped`","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the parent domain contains additional logic for switching between cases of child state,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"prefer "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/ReducerProtocol\/ifCaseLet(_:action:then:fileID:line:)"},{"type":"text","text":", which better ensures that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"child logic runs "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"before"}]},{"type":"text","text":" any parent logic can replace child state:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Reduce { state, action in","  switch action {","  case .loggedIn(.quitButtonTapped):","    state = .loggedOut(LoggedOut.State())","  \/\/ ...","  }","}",".ifCaseLet(\/State.loggedIn, action: \/Action.